# Project Awareness and Documentation Guide

## Initial Project Review
- Always start by reading [PLANNING.md](mdc:PLANNING.md) to understand:
  - Current architecture
  - Tech stack (Astro + Tailwind + Markdown + Bun)
  - Design principles
  - Project goals
- Review [INFORMATION.md](mdc:INFORMATION.md) to understand:
  - Company information and mission
  - Service offerings and pricing
  - Content structure and requirements
  - Brand voice and messaging

## Task Management
- Review [TASKS.md](mdc:TASKS.md) before beginning any work
- Document new tasks with:
  - Brief description
  - Today's date
  - Appropriate section placement
- Ensure content tasks reference [INFORMATION.md](mdc:INFORMATION.md)

## Project Structure Compliance
- Follow naming conventions from [PLANNING.md](mdc:PLANNING.md)
- Maintain consistent file structure
- Adhere to modular layout guidelines
- Ensure consistency across:
  - Markdown content
  - Astro components
  - Layouts

## Documentation Requirements
- Keep [README.md](mdc:README.md) updated with:
  - Setup steps
  - Dependencies (e.g., npm to bun changes)
  - Key usage instructions
  - Environment requirements
  - Development workflow

## Project Context
- Maintain awareness of project goals
- Follow established design principles
- Keep documentation in sync with code changes
- Update relevant documentation when making architectural changes
- Ensure content aligns with [INFORMATION.md](mdc:INFORMATION.md)
